"{\"uid\": \"gbnews.com-celebrity-bbc-olympics-commentary-complaints-rower-helen-glover-outdated-misogyny\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Labour-run council shoots down claim migrant cultures 'do not respect women'  BBC Olympics: Remarks about Helen Glover have sparked outrage  BBC  ByAlex Davies,  Published: 01/08/2024  Updated: 01/08/2024  Olympic rower Helen Glover bagged a silver medal alongside her teammates on Thursday  Several BBC viewers have expressed their dismay at the corporation's Olympics presenting team's turn of phrase when discussing rower Helen Glover, 38.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 442, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 78, \"end\": 81, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"score\": 0.99999999833517, \"rank\": 1.009327387078362e-09, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\"}, {\"begin\": 106, \"end\": 118, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\", \"score\": 0.9968858553495725, \"rank\": 0.0031234382808593376, \"text\": \"Helen Glover\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\"}, {\"begin\": 141, \"end\": 144, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"score\": 0.99999999833517, \"rank\": 1.009327387078362e-09, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\"}, {\"begin\": 220, \"end\": 232, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\", \"score\": 0.9968858553495725, \"rank\": 0.0031234382808593376, \"text\": \"Helen Glover\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\"}, {\"begin\": 300, \"end\": 303, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"score\": 0.99999999833517, \"rank\": 1.009327387078362e-09, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\"}, {\"begin\": 425, \"end\": 437, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\", \"score\": 0.9968858553495725, \"rank\": 0.0031234382808593376, \"text\": \"Helen Glover\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On Thursday morning, Glover was hoping to bag a historic third Olympic gold medal when she took to the water alongside teammates Esme Booth, Sam Redgrave and Rebecca Shorten.\", \"from\": 444, \"to\": 618, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 465, \"end\": 471, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Glover\", \"score\": 0.999999951956853, \"rank\": 4.801238568716114e-08, \"text\": \"Glover\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Glover\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Glover\"}, {\"begin\": 585, \"end\": 588, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Winchester\", \"score\": 0.8251057292844954, \"rank\": 0.21194496723043424, \"text\": \"Sam\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Winchester\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Winchester\"}, {\"begin\": 602, \"end\": 617, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebecca_Shorten\", \"score\": 0.9999947512179875, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rebecca Shorten\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebecca_Shorten\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebecca_Shorten\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In what was a nail-biting finish, the Team GB rowers were pipped to the post by the Netherlands team but the four were all smiles as they celebrated their silver medal win.The four athletes added to Team GB's medal haul just hours after fellow rowers Mathilda Hodgkins Byrne and Rebecca Wilde secured bronze in the Women's Double Sculls.However, what should have been a joyous occasion for BBC viewers and Team GB athletes was soured somewhat by the likes of pundit Matthew Pinsent and the race's commentators' \\\"continuous focus\\\" on the fact Glover was a mum-of-three.Pinsent was the first to raise the fact ahead of the race when he said: \\\"So Helen Glover, Esme Booth, Sam Redgrave and Rebecca Shorten about to go in the women's coxless four.BBC Olympics: Helen Glover won silver alongside her teammates in the Women's Four|BBC\\\"And Glover, of course, a mother as well, it seems to be a morning of parental athletes, they have all been through the mill to get here.\", \"from\": 620, \"to\": 1585, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 658, \"end\": 665, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999999999809006, \"rank\": 1.8535874827389554e-11, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 704, \"end\": 715, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.9996760051779254, \"rank\": 0.0002921368686171404, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}, {\"begin\": 819, \"end\": 826, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999999999809006, \"rank\": 1.8535874827389554e-11, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 871, \"end\": 879, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matilda_australia\", \"score\": 0.7908240701537502, \"rank\": 0.1989304812833776, \"text\": \"Mathilda\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matilda_australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matilda_australia\"}, {\"begin\": 880, \"end\": 888, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hodgkins,_Illinois\", \"score\": 0.9806335237791598, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hodgkins\", \"types\": [\"Q532\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hodgkins,_Illinois\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hodgkins,_Illinois\"}, {\"begin\": 889, \"end\": 894, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Byrne\", \"score\": 0.9999999988644959, \"rank\": 1.1355574970278153e-09, \"text\": \"Byrne\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Byrne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Byrne\"}, {\"begin\": 899, \"end\": 906, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebecca_Napier\", \"score\": 0.9752378093448952, \"rank\": 0.016602908573800965, \"text\": \"Rebecca\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebecca_Napier\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebecca_Napier\"}, {\"begin\": 907, \"end\": 912, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oscar_Wilde\", \"score\": 0.9999999954125087, \"rank\": 4.552877292061707e-09, \"text\": \"Wilde\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oscar_Wilde\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oscar_Wilde\"}, {\"begin\": 1010, \"end\": 1013, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"score\": 0.99999999833517, \"rank\": 1.009327387078362e-09, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\"}, {\"begin\": 1026, \"end\": 1033, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_