1389, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\", \"score\": 0.9968858553495725, \"rank\": 0.0031234382808593376, \"text\": \"Helen Glover\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"He and his co-star then reflected on Glover's Olympic record before the race began.But as the rowers entered the final 250 metres of the race, the female commentator referred to Glover's parenting again: \\\"Helen Glover's a mum, she will be thinking of her three children screaming from the bank.\", \"from\": 1585, \"to\": 1880, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1623, \"end\": 1629, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Glover\", \"score\": 0.999999951956853, \"rank\": 4.801238568716114e-08, \"text\": \"Glover\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Glover\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Glover\"}, {\"begin\": 1764, \"end\": 1770, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Glover\", \"score\": 0.999999951956853, \"rank\": 4.801238568716114e-08, \"text\": \"Glover\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Glover\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Glover\"}, {\"begin\": 1791, \"end\": 1803, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\", \"score\": 0.9968858553495725, \"rank\": 0.0031234382808593376, \"text\": \"Helen Glover\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Several fans were left furious with the attention given to the fact Glover had children, including one angered viewer who penned on X: \\\"Can the BBC rowing commentator just shut the f*** up about the rowers being mums thanks.\", \"from\": 1880, \"to\": 2105, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1949, \"end\": 1955, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Glover\", \"score\": 0.999999951956853, \"rank\": 4.801238568716114e-08, \"text\": \"Glover\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Glover\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Glover\"}, {\"begin\": 2025, \"end\": 2028, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"score\": 0.99999999833517, \"rank\": 1.009327387078362e-09, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"BBC Olympics: Helen Glover and her husband Steve Backshall celebrated with their three children|PAA second suggested the remarks were outdated as they fumed: \\\"It's 2024 and, once again, the BBC commentators are focusing on the fact that the women are 'mums'.\", \"from\": 2105, \"to\": 2364, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2106, \"end\": 2109, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"score\": 0.99999999833517, \"rank\": 1.009327387078362e-09, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\"}, {\"begin\": 2120, \"end\": 2132, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\", \"score\": 0.9968858553495725, \"rank\": 0.0031234382808593376, \"text\": \"Helen Glover\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\"}, {\"begin\": 2149, \"end\": 2164, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_Backshall\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Steve Backshall\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_Backshall\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_Backshall\"}, {\"begin\": 2296, \"end\": 2299, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"score\": 0.99999999833517, \"rank\": 1.009327387078362e-09, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"They have not mentioned with the male rowers how many kids they have.\", \"from\": 2364, \"to\": 2434, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Why is this a thing?\", \"from\": 2435, \"to\": 2455, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They are incredible athletes.\", \"from\": 2456, \"to\": 2485, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That should be the focus, not their ability to reproduce.\", \"from\": 2486, \"to\": 2543, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Elsewhere, a third raged: \\\"Why are the BBC commentators going ON ON about the rowers being 'mums'?\", \"from\": 2543, \"to\": 2642, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2583, \"end\": 2586, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"score\": 0.99999999833517, \"rank\": 1.009327387078362e-09, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is so condescending!\", \"from\": 2643, \"to\": 2666, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That's it, ladies, your life does not have to end when you have a kid... #BBCOlympics #Paris2024 \\\"And a fourth echoed: \\\"I feel like the BBC's continuous focus on how helen glover being a mum affects her as an athlete is a bit ridiculous when you consider her husband is steve backshall who's always off in some jungle fighting venomous snakes.\", \"from\": 2667, \"to\": 3010, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2803, \"end\": 2806, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"score\": 0.99999999833517, \"rank\": 1.009327387078362e-09, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\"}, {\"begin\": 2937, \"end\": 2952, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_Backshall\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"steve backshall\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_Backshall\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_Backshall\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"BBC commentator mentioning several times that one of the GB rowers this morning is a 'mum'.\", \"from\": 3010, \"to\": 3102, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3011, \"end\": 3014, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"score\": 0.99999999833517, \"rank\": 1.009327387078362e-09, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\"}, {\"begin\": 3068, \"end\": 3070, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.6040685955456929, \"rank\": 0.6554411298924989, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What's that to do with anything?\", \"from\": 3103, \"to\": 3135, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"No mention of male rowers being 'dads',\\\" a fifth questioned.Before a sixth hit out: \\\"Really p***ed me off that earlier in the games the BBC referred to Helen Glover as 'mum of three' and not 'double Olympic Champion'.\\\"\", \"from\": 3136, \"to\": 3354, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3272, \"end\": 3275, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"score\": 0.99999999833517, \"rank\": 1.009327387078362e-09, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"h